&lt;h4 class=&quot;margin-top-40 margin-bottom-8 textH4-3Bngsz headingDefault-2s3GxE sizeLarge-2FUtr2 lineTiny-1v9oiX weightSemiBold-19z6Hb&quot;&gt;About Us&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Discord is a voice, video and text app that helps friends and communities come together to hang out and explore their interests — from artists and activists, to study groups, sneakerheads, plant parents, and more. With 150 million monthly users across 19 million active communities, called servers, Discord has grown to become one of the most popular communications services in the world. Discord was built without selling ads or user data and instead, offers a premium subscription called Nitro that gives users special perks like higher quality streams and fun customizations.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We’re working toward an inclusive world where no one feels like an outsider, where genuine human connection is a click, text chat, or voice call away. A place where everyone can find belonging. Challenging? Heck yes. Rewarding? Double heck yes. It’s a mission that gives us the chance to positively impact millions of people all over the world. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;So if this strikes a chord with you, come build belonging with us!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Discord is your place to talk. Whether you&#39;re part of a school club, gaming group, worldwide art community, or just a handful of friends that want to spend time together, millions of people use Discord every day to create connections, hang out, and talk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At the heart of Discord&#39;s communities is Safety. The Safety team at Discord is responsible for ensuring users find belonging by minimizing exposure to spam and other forms of platform abuse. We are excited to find others passionate about making sure Discord is a safe and welcoming place for our users and hope you can join us on this mission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a Director of Product to join us and lead our Safety Product Management team. You will responsible for creating a vision, crafting a strategy, building systems and features, ideating creative solutions, and building a product group to advance our mission towards Safety at Discord.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll be doing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide the product philosophy, vision, and strategy for products and features that make Discord the safest platform for people to find community and belonging.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attract, build, manage, and develop a team of talented product managers to deliver on both fundamental and novel approaches to user &amp;amp; platform Safety.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage multiple products and priorities, scale teams, and ensure your org is effective, healthy and set up for success by establishing clear and measurable goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate clearly roadmaps, priorities, experiments and decisions across a wide spectrum of audiences from partner teams to executive levels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead a cross-functional organization of engineers, designers, and data scientists to build robust systems, tools and products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with other product teams across our organization, such as Communities, Growth, Creators, and Premium Products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Empathize, engage and cultivate relationships with our users to deeply understand their needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you should have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passionate about Discord and about keeping users safe from abuse (including spam)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to thrive in ambiguous environments, excited about finding solutions to complex problems, and then executing on them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of experience building and shipping great software, including responsibilities driving prioritization, trade-offs, and timelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6+ years of experience hiring, managing, and developing both individual contributors and senior product leaders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6+ years of experience focused on platforms (consumer, communications, or social)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of achieving impact through empowering customers with innovative solutions**.**&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to analyze and synthesize data in order to set strategic goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience presenting to senior executive audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated technical proficiency and effectiveness working closely with engineers and managers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong product sense and pride in understanding your customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonus Points&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Subject matter expertise in Trust &amp;amp; Safety (and/or related areas such as Spam, Abuse, or Integrity) to lead our product area &amp;amp; drive alignment with engineering, data science, design, and XFN stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building and growing social and/or online communication products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BA/BS in Computer Science, Engineering, or relevant technical experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Entrepreneurial experience building consumer applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;(New York City only*) Minimum salary of $206,000/year + equity and benefits Note: Disclosure as required by NYC Pay Transparency Law &lt;br&gt;(Colorado only*) Minimum salary of $164,800/year + equity and benefits *Note: Disclosure as required by sb19-085(8-5-20).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
