&lt;div&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;With 150 million monthly users across 19 million active communities, Discord has grown to become one of the most popular communications services in the world.&amp;nbsp; We’re building an outstanding product marketing organization to help shape and scale Discord to diverse communities around the world.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;At the heart of these communities are the admins and creators who build and manage them. We’ve been building more and more features and tools to ensure these communities can be successful on Discord including newer features that allow them to directly monetize. An important part of that ecosystem are the business programs we build to onboard, engage, and structure our relationships which include our existing Verified Program and a need to build a new Monetization Program.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We are looking for a Manager, Creator Programs who can come join the team and help define the strategy and operations for how these programs should work. You will need to work cross-functionally across product, operations, legal/policy and marketing teams to help identify current gaps and ways to improve our Verified Program as well as build a new monetization program from the ground up. This is a foundational role that will build and shape the strategy for core business programs at Discord.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;You will report to the Head of Creator &amp;amp; Community Product Marketing &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h4 class=&quot;margin-top-40 margin-bottom-8 textH4-3Bngsz headingDefault-2s3GxE sizeLarge-2FUtr2 lineTiny-1v9oiX weightSemiBold-19z6Hb&quot;&gt;What you&#39;ll be doing&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Evolve and structure our Verified Program: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;help tackle major strategic decisions around Verified program like:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Who should be allowed verification and why?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;How should we structure support models for Verified Servers?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;How should product features should or should not be a part of this program?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build a new monetization program: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;as we expand our premium memberships feature (and new monetization features) globally we will need to build out a program to help us determine:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Who should be allowed access to monetization and why?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;What support segmentation should we build for these communities?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;What features/products are needed to support this program&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Identify new product needs to ensure we meet the needs of this audience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Evaluate team needs/structure: &lt;/strong&gt;help identify team structure and needs moving forward including potential new hires to this team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;h4 class=&quot;margin-top-40 margin-bottom-8 textH4-3Bngsz headingDefault-2s3GxE sizeLarge-2FUtr2 lineTiny-1v9oiX weightSemiBold-19z6Hb&quot;&gt;You&#39;ll thrive in this role if...&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;You love solving new problems where we are still defining the roadmap&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;You have 6+ years in product marketing or business strategy/operations ideally including experience building or managing a team&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;You have experience building scalable programs that reach a creator or business audience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;You have experience working with partnership and operation teams to build new support and business models&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;You’re able to build clear business frameworks using data to help structure cross functional team thinking&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
