&lt;h2&gt;Discord is looking for an experienced, driven, and curious Data Scientist to join the Messaging &amp;amp; Experience team. The Messaging &amp;amp; Experience data science team concentrates on supporting core Discord experiences for both internal teams and Discord users. As a team, we strive to partner closely with our area leads to help drive optimal strategy and decision making. From working on measuring the efficacy of new messaging-related product feature launches, to driving the quantitative success measurement of our very first console integration, we are looking for hungry data scientists to help us build strong foundations and deliver value! We strive to help reenforce and measure Discord core values across areas such as messaging, gaming, and internal operations. Check out our blog about how our team informs strategy &amp;amp; innovation at Discord &lt;a class=&quot;notion-link-token notion-enable-hover&quot; href=&quot;https://discord.com/blog/how-data-science-informs-strategy-innovation-at-discord&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-token-index=&quot;1&quot; data-reactroot=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;link-annotation-unknown-block-id-371899876&quot;&gt;here&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;!&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;What you&#39;ll be doing&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;ul1&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with engineering, product and operations teams through the full lifecycle of data analytics from ideation and exploratory analysis, to building dashboards and reports&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define KPIs and diagnostic metrics that help improve the user experience, encapsulating these measures in clean, crisp and performant dashboards that provide the company with timely and actionable information&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dive deep into our data to understand our users, their patterns of guild/server usage, and the ways they use our platform to communicate with friends&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use our amazing infrastructure to quickly and easily build custom data sets to monitor novel product features and processes (internal/external)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive strategic thinking in various areas, including a strong focus in understanding the gaming ecosystem and the various ways we can drive value for gamers of all types!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively socialize insights, dashboards, and reports with technical and non-technical audiences, soliciting feedback on areas to improve&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a champion of A/B testing and help groups throughout the company design, analyze, and interpret A/B tests correctly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with data and engineering teams to design scalable and future-proof instrumentation, along with data assets that drive an understanding and measurement of the metric trees in our areas of coverage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;You&#39;ll Thrive In This Role If (not hard qualifications - if you&#39;re not sure, please apply!)&lt;/h4&gt;
