&lt;h2&gt;As a Safety engineer, your focus is on the long-term systems, operations, and APIs of the Anti-Abuse team. Your customers will be other engineers and operators who will use your products to grow safety. Come for the interesting projects, stay for the important mission. You report to the Safety Platform Manager.&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;You Will:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build UIs and APIs in React and Python around our in-house, real-time, abuse detection platform that allow us to identify and &lt;span id=&quot;d6eced84cc88fd1e9203de4b4cb58aec&quot; class=&quot;editor-module-hl-red-solid&quot;&gt;take action&lt;/span&gt; against abuse.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate abuse data understanding by building easy-to-understand analysis toolsets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with analysts and other engineers to identify bottlenecks in their workflow and implement elegant solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Move quickly to respond to the evolving landscape of abuse on Discord.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
