&lt;h2&gt;Gamers of all kinds have been at the heart of Discord since we got started. Our small, nimble, Games team is focused on building the next version of Discord for the needs of gamers to play together and be together. We are a new team and are looking for new engineers who want to build new features for gamers!&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;We are trying to achieve a lot, but we are in a marathon, not a sprint, so good work/life balance is just as important as working with smart, experienced people (like you!?). Our business is growing very quickly, and we are growing quickly to support it. Join our team, and you can help us build the next generation of Discord.&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;To learn more about Discord Engineering, take a look at our &lt;a href=&quot;https://discord.com/category/engineering&quot;&gt;engineering blog&lt;/a&gt;!&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;What you&#39;ll do&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build new features across our iOS, Android, Web apps. We work across the stack, but it&#39;s ok if you don&#39;t know all of our technology on day one!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architecture elegant and maintainable code with focus on autonomy and support from the team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Propose and champion improvements to the product, engineering, and process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work on meaningful projects that help Discord become the unified social layer of cross-platform gaming.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with designers, product managers and other engineers to create delightful interfaces and experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fearlessly dive into the unknown alongside intelligent engineers challenging themselves and people around you.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will report to our Engineering Manager of Games&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Things we look for&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4+ years of full-stack experience. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We&#39;re a multi-platform team, so it&#39;s important to have a solid understanding of the development frameworks and fundamentals of one or more of our platforms: web (React, TypeScript), Android (React Native, Kotlin), iOS (React Native, Objective-C, Swift), and backend (Python and some Elixir).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience building and shipping product features.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; Especially products at large scale or in real-time applications and on projects that have a lot of ambiguity.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A focus on impact&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;. You have an eye for what changes can bring a product from good to great. You collaborate closely with product managers, designers, analysts, and other engineers to define great solutions to business problems&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You&#39;re likely a gamer.&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; All kinds of people use Discord, and this team is focused on the gamers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;New York City residents only: Minimum salary of $186,000/year + equity and benefits. Disclosure as required by NYC Pay Transparency Law. Colorado residents only: Minimum salary of $148,800/year + equity and benefits. Disclosure as required by sb19-085(8-5-20).&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;h4 class=&quot;margin-top-40 margin-bottom-8 textH4-3Bngsz headingDefault-2s3GxE sizeLarge-2FUtr2 lineTiny-1v9oiX weightSemiBold-19z6Hb&quot;&gt;Benefits and Perks&lt;/h4&gt;
