&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Discord is a voice, video and text app that helps friends and communities come together to hang out and explore their interests — from artists and activists, to study groups, sneakerheads, plant parents, and more. With 150 million monthly users across 19 million active communities, called servers, Discord has grown to become one of the most popular communications services in the world. Discord was built without selling ads or user data and instead, offers a premium subscription called Nitro that gives users special perks like higher quality streams and fun customizations.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We’re working toward an inclusive world where no one feels like an outsider, where genuine human connection is a click, text chat, or voice call away. A place where everyone can find belonging. Challenging? Heck yes. Rewarding? Double heck yes. It’s a mission that gives us the chance to positively impact millions of people all over the world. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;So if this strikes a chord with you, come build belonging with us!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Discord is your place to talk. Whether you&#39;re part of a school club, gaming group, worldwide art community, or just a handful of friends that want to spend time together, millions of people use Discord every day to find community, hang out, and talk.&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;At the heart of Discord&#39;s communities is Safety. The Safety team at Discord ensures users find belonging by minimizing exposure to spam and other forms of platform abuse. We are excited to find others passionate about making sure Discord is a safe and welcoming place for our users and hope you can join us on this mission.&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;As a Specialized Program Leader, you will report directly to the Director of Trust and Safety and you will hone an understanding of all abuse areas for Safety Operations while evolving the ongoing structure and scale of our specialized teams.&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h4 class=&quot;margin-top-40 margin-bottom-8 textH4-3Bngsz headingDefault-2s3GxE sizeLarge-2FUtr2 lineTiny-1v9oiX weightSemiBold-19z6Hb&quot;&gt;What you&#39;ll be doing&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and scale our specialized safety teams focused on a variety of abuse verticals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use quantitative and qualitative methods to identify gaps across teams, develop root cause analyses, and enable continuous improvements in response to changing circumstances&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee strategic projects from initial conception through implementation across multiple areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with Policy, Product, Engineering, and Trust &amp;amp; Safety teams in the development of operational policies, tools, and solutions; frequently collaborate with additional internal teams to manage expectations and drive consensus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate and present to senior leadership on the important metrics and progress of each specialized team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
