&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communities play a huge part in Discord&#39;s mission. Millions of people come to Discord every day to hang out in communities for all kinds of interests, from servers where thousands of Harry Potter fans connect and geek out, to servers where students practice speaking new languages with native speakers halfway across the world.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;At the heart of communities are the admins and moderators who build and run them. The Online Communities Group at Discord &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;is responsible for empowering&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; these creators to build thriving spaces that many people call their second home. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We believe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; helping creators succeed is &lt;/strong&gt;important&lt;strong&gt; to creating more healthy communities.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Discord is looking for a technical, creative, hands-on, and mission-focused Staff Engineer to guide the technical direction of our Communities Product. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;build&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;out&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;exciting&lt;strong&gt; features used by millions of communities across Discord, and setting the technical vision for Communities on Discord&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What you&#39;ll do&lt;/h3&gt;
